      "writtenOn": "2020-09-28T19:00:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Interesting! I tried this experiment locally. I\u0027m using goma but I can control the parallelism via -j.\n\nWith -j 1, it was very very slow, but the time was clearly spent rebuilding all the FP gencode. I eventually canceled it.\nWith -j 8, I get build times of ~34 seconds.\nWith -j 333 (my usual), I get build times of ~15 seconds.\n\nIt didn\u0027t look like the golden-files actions were a significant portion of the times in any event. Linking seemed to be the biggest blocking event. I don\u0027t know how much of the timing is invalidated by goma caching results.",
